Pleopods typical of genus; ventrolateral lobe of protopods expanded in spawning molt; endopod of first pleopod subtriangular, without appendix interna. Uropod (
Fig. 1
) with both rami slightly overreaching posterior margin of telson.

The number of the meral spines on the third pereopod is variable from three to six (
Fig. 19
), but the majority of the specimens (88.0 %) have four or five spines. Six specimens ( 10 %) have six spines; only one specimen has six spines only on the left side, and thus this condition is rather unusual for this species.
